<p><strong>How to set Facility Status to &ldquo;Non-Regulated&rdquo;</strong></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Sign-in to CERS Regulator.</li>
<li>Locate facility record by searching, via the &ldquo;Facilities&rdquo; Search/selecting the &ldquo;Facilities&rdquo; button from the CERS Regulator menu bar.</li>
<li>Open the facility record, by selecting the CERS ID button from the Facilities Search results.</li>
<li>Select the &ldquo;Manage Facility&rdquo; link, from the menu on the left-hand side of the Facility &ldquo;Summary&rdquo; page.</li>
<li>Select the &ldquo;Non-Regulated Facilities&rdquo; link, from the &ldquo;Manage Facility&rdquo; page.</li>
<li>Confirm on the following page(s), to remove the reporting requirements for this facility record and remove the facility from its current Business Organization.</li>
</ol>